# Component Architecture

## Three-Layer System

### Layer 1 ‚Äî UI Primitives (`src/components/ui/`)
Small, reusable, content-free building blocks. Never hardcode colors ‚Äî use CSS variables.
```
Button.jsx        ‚Äî variants: primary | secondary | outline | ghost ‚Äî sizes: sm | md | lg
Badge.jsx         ‚Äî variants: default | accent
SectionHeader.jsx ‚Äî eyebrow + title + subtitle, align: center | left
Card.jsx          ‚Äî base card wrapper
Input.jsx         ‚Äî styled text/email input
Textarea.jsx      ‚Äî styled textarea
Label.jsx         ‚Äî form label
Accordion.jsx     ‚Äî native <details>/<summary>, zero JS
index.js          ‚Äî barrel export for all primitives
```

### Layer 2 ‚Äî Sections (`src/components/sections/`)
Full page sections that compose UI primitives. Never write raw `<button>` ‚Äî use `<Button>`.
```
Hero.jsx          ‚Äî full-bleed bg image, priority loaded, stats bar at bottom
Services.jsx      ‚Äî service cards grid
Performance.jsx   ‚Äî PageSpeed proof section, accepts screenshotSrc prop
Process.jsx       ‚Äî numbered steps
Pricing.jsx       ‚Äî two-column subscription vs lump sum
FAQ.jsx           ‚Äî accordion items
CTA.jsx           ‚Äî contact form (Web3Forms, 'use client')
Footer.jsx        ‚Äî logo, nav links, legal links
```

### Layer 3 ‚Äî Layout (`src/components/layout/`)
```
Header.jsx        ‚Äî fixed nav, 3-col grid, CSS-only mobile menu, logo-shine animation
```

## Header Logo
The logo uses a CSS animation class `logo-shine` defined in `globals.css`.
- "Vantage" renders as plain `text-text`
- "Web Designs" gets the `logo-shine` class ‚Äî gold text with a sweeping white glisten every 8s
- Do not remove or alter this without updating `globals.css`

## Theming
All values reference CSS variables from `globals.css`. Never hardcode colors, fonts, or spacing.

**Available tokens:**
- Colors: `--color-bg`, `--color-surface`, `--color-surface-2`, `--color-border`, `--color-primary`, `--color-primary-dark`, `--color-text`, `--color-muted`
- Fonts: `--font-sans`, `--font-heading`
- Spacing: `--spacing-section`
- Radius: `--radius-sm`, `--radius-md`, `--radius-lg`, `--radius-xl`
- Shadows: `--shadow-card`, `--shadow-glow`

```jsx
/* ‚úÖ GOOD */
<section className="bg-surface py-[var(--spacing-section)]">
<h2 className="font-heading text-primary">

/* ‚ùå BAD */
<section className="bg-[#09090f] py-24">
<h2 className="font-syne text-amber-500">
```

## Rebranding a Template
When copying this repo for a new client template:
1. Update `src/utils/constants.js` ‚Äî `BASE_URL`, `SITE_NAME`, `CONTACT_EMAIL`
2. Update CSS tokens in `globals.css` ‚Äî colors, fonts
3. Replace `src/styles/assets/hero-img.webp` with client's hero image
4. Add `public/preview.png` (1200x630) and `public/favicon.png`
5. Update `.env.local` ‚Äî `NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY`, Notion keys if blog is active
6. Update `src/app/layout.js` metadata ‚Äî title, description, OG tags
7. Update section copy as needed ‚Äî all hardcoded in each section component

## Client / Server
- Default to Server Components
- Add `'use client'` only when using hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- `CTA.jsx` is intentionally `'use client'` ‚Äî it manages form state
- Never add `'use client'` just because it feels familiar
